FBIS4-41035 "drsov120_f_94014" FBIS-SOV-94-120 Daily Report 22 Jun 1994 National Affairs Kravchuk's Economic Adviser Urges Increased Pace of Reform Kravchuk's Economic Adviser Urges Increased Pace of Reform WS2206115094 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in Ukrainian 1000 GMT 22 Jun 94 WS2206115094 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network Ukrainian BFN [Text] Foreign investors will only begin to deposit their capital in the Ukrainian economy if there is political and economic stabilization. This was stated in an interview with the UKRAINSKIYE VEDOMOSTI magazine by Bohdan Havrylyshyn, an independent adviser to the Ukrainian president. He noted that if the current pace of reform is maintained, Ukraine may end up in international isolation and be transformed into an economic refugee. Bohdan Havrylyshyn emphasized that without conducting deep economic transformations, Ukraine cannot count on financial assistance from the West.
